// Talkatoo% mode (Phase 3): substitution at the speech-resolve chokepoint.
// GameDataFunction::tryFindShineMessage(actor*, sys*, world_id, index)
// returns the per-shine display char16_t* for the speech bubble. We
// trampoline it and replace the return value with an AP-pool moon name
// when the caller is a Poetter (Talkatoo) actor.
_ZN16GameDataFunction19tryFindShineMessageEPKN2al9LiveActorEPKNS0_17IUseMessageSystemEii

// Poetter (Talkatoo) primary vtable. Read at install time via
// hk::ro::lookupSymbol — used as a range filter to scope substitution to
// Talkatoo-only callsites. The trampoline above runs for every caller
// (cutscenes, pause menu, hint UI), so without this we'd substitute moon
// names project-wide.
_ZTV7Poetter

